{
  "text": "ZRA NB3 localization to DNA is amplified upon induction of replication stress through PIP box-and APIM-dependent binding of PCNA [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . ZRA NB3 also contains an NPL4 zinc-finger motif that preferentially binds K63 polyubiquitinated PCNA and is required for its localization to sites of replication stress [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
  "correct_citation": {
